Text: Wha—?! You showed up as if right on cue!
This Lady Karen incident is starting to smell fishy!

I'm not sure who sent you, but it's high time you
realized you lack the power to stop me!
...Guess she seems fine for now?
Yes, she's fine.

...Annerose is a tough one. Looks like we might not
need to have her back until the Children arrive.
Hmm...
What's with the long face?

The idea of using such a pure-hearted knight to
further our plan...

Oh? That's not something I'd expect to hear from a
former Child and aristocrat.

Or maybe deep down, you yearned to lead a life like
Annerose's, dedicated wholeheartedly to pursuing
justice?
How dare you...?!
Looks like I hit a nerve.
...Urk!

Anyway, you're getting too invested. What's in it for
you, anyway? What can that dark knight offer you?

She could inherit my pride as one of Velgalta's Seven
Blades... My pride as a knight!
Pride, huh...

Isn't the concept of pride just another convenient
notion exploited by the Cult to exert control over
the world?

Yes, I was once on the exploiting side, using the
power of aristocracy and the pride of knighthood...

But Annerose... She wields the power of Velgalta
knighthood as a simple dark knight, driven solely
by her desire to right the world.
...So, yes...No. 122, you're right.

Maybe I do envy Annerose's path while, at the same
time, wishing that she continues to embrace her role
as a knight.

As my successor in the Seven Blades, I hope she
accomplishes what I couldn't—to fight with pride.

Hmm... Is that how it works? Personally, I find that
concept, or should I say worldview, hard to grasp.

...To be honest, I don't possess or even understand
feelings of pride or passion.

But maybe protecting someone else's pride from the
shadows is also...a kind of pride in itself?

Protecting someone else's pride is a form of pride as
well!

Jeez, you've really done a number on me, Miss Former
Baroness. I can't believe I'm letting myself get drawn
into something so silly...
Anyway, looks like it's time to wrap up our chitchat.
Right... They're attacking in full force!

The number of reinforcements is on a completely
different scale compared to previous attacks. Their
strategy seems to be to exhaust her in a prolonged
battle and then overwhelm her with sheer numbers.

It appears they've even unleashed monsters...
Let's provide backup!
You bet—
Haaaah!
Aaaagghh...!
...What is this? What's going on?

The surrounding enemy numbers were initially growing,
but now they're decreasing more rapidly than I can
eliminate them...!
Dieee!
Not happening!
Gaaaahh...!

I'm not sure what's happening, but...is someone
aiding me?!
...Not on my watch!
Ugfff...!

No. 111! Don't get so worked up! You're getting
too close to the individual we're supposed to be
protecting!

I won't let the likes of you sully her unblemished
pride!
Wh-Who the hell is this...?!

Make yourself less conspicuous! If she finds you,
we're in trouble—
Found you! You must be the leader of this squad!
Erk!
Come on, let's settle this... Huhhh?!
(We've been found out! This is bad!)
...Lady Karen...!

(Wha...?! They're teaming up? What the heck is going
on?!)
